{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Unless Tag - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Unless Tag</h1>

<p>The unless tag is the logical inverse of the if tag. It renders content when a condition is false.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% unless .condition %}...{% end %}
{% unless .condition %}...{% else %}...{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>The unless tag evaluates a condition and renders content if the condition is falsy (false, nil, empty, or zero).</p>

<h2>Examples</h2>

<h3>Basic Unless</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% unless .hidden %}Visible{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"hidden": false}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Visible</p>

<h3>Unless with Else</h3>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% unless .error %}
  Success
{% else %}
  Error occurred
{% end %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Equivalent to "if not"</li>
  <li>Supports else clause for alternative content</li>
  <li>Common use: checking for nil/empty conditions</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/tags/if">if tag</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/tags/for">for tag</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
